snippet.title: The Goonies
snippet.description: Steven Spielberg, Richard Donner (Lethal Weapon films) and ChrisColumbus (Harry Potter films) collaborate to create an epic childen'sadventure of subterranean caverns, sunken galleons and a fortune in lostpirate treasure waiting to be found by a group of friends known as theGoonies. With brothers Mikey (Sean Astin) and Brand's (Josh Brolin)house slated for demolition by greedy land developers, the boys decidetheir only hope lies in finding a long-lost treasure. They uncover atreasure map and with their friends descend to a subterranean sea and anabandoned galleon in this fun-filled, fast-paced adventure.

snippet.title: The Wiggles, Choo Choo Trains, Propeller Planes, and Toot Toot Chugga Chugga Big Red Car!
snippet.description: Join The Wiggles on a dancing, singing and travelling adventure. Go for a ride in the Big Red Car and 'Emma's Bowmobile, Beep Beep!'. Take a Wiggly plane ride to the Australian outback or go soaring through space in a 'Rocket Ship' and go walking on the moon. This special release inspires children to use their creative energy and imagination to think of different modes of travel ‚Äì driving, flying, riding, walking, galloping and dancing. The Wiggles introduce new friends such as, Paul Nunnari, performing incredible tricks in his wheelchair; Richie Allan and his family, dancing to 'Old Man Emu' with Australian music legend, John Williamson and driving in the Big Red Car to the lovely sounds of Canadian trio, The East Pointers - Koady, Jake and Tim. This really is a Wiggly expedition full of fun, laughter, singing, dancing and travel. So, hop in, seatbelts on and take a ride with Choo Choo Trains, Propeller Planes and Toot Toot Chugga Chugga Big Red Car!

snippet.title: 12 Min Kids Exercise: Morning Fun (Let s Get Active!)
snippet.description:
Kids need physical activity right from the morning, the moment they wake up. These exercises will get them busy and will also provide an outlet for their endless energy! 

Also, working out everyday is a great way to boos kids' metabolism, burn unnecessary calories and make sure they have a fit body and strong enough to face the daily challenges!

Good luck and let's begin the workout! 💪

snippet.title: Let's Get Fit | Version 3 | Count to 100 | Exercises for Kids | 100 Days of School | Jack Hartmann
snippet.description:
Your favorite count to 100 by ones song, with new exercises that are great for the classroom or at physical education. I consulted with physical education teachers in developing this new count to 100 song.

This count to 100 song includes some creative and fun new exercises and some physical education positions that are required in PE. I have included cross lateral movements that are so important for body and brain connections and improved brain coordination. Studies have linked increased academic performance to cross lateral movements.    

We are so pleased this count to 100 song has become so popular all over the world. Children seem to love the energy of the music that is great for motivating children to move. I try to do my part and do the song with energy and enthusiasm too.

Exercise is so important for our children. I believe in it, and try to swim, run or bike everyday. I say the numbers very clearly so children can understand and say them with me as we count to 100.

Have fun and keep moving to our Count to 100
Let's Get Fit version 3!

snippet.title: Trump Card
snippet.description: A specter is haunting America-the specter of socialism. At first glance, this seems incredible. The twentieth century is seen as the century in which capitalism defeated socialism. Socialist regimes collapsed around the world. Today socialism is confined to failing societies such as Cuba, North Korea, and Venezuela. Yet leading candidates and media figures are enthusiastic about moving America toward socialism. They have a raft of proposals for doing this: Medicare for all, universal basic income, free college, and the Green New Deal. This movie will expose the ideology and tactics of the new socialism. It will explain the temptation of socialism-an age of abundance in which we all get something for nothing-and show why the socialist society is a mirage. Socialism produces deprivation, conformity, and tyranny. More than a critique of socialism, the movie will also make a moral defense of capitalism and show how capitalism, not socialism, is the best way to have prosperity and social justice. Narrated by Dinesh D'Souza and featuring eye-opening interviews, dramatic recreations, and comical animated illustrations, this film will be a timely, riveting, and entertaining look at the biggest issue dividing America today.

snippet.title: 5 minute thigh workout to sculpt strong ballet legs
snippet.description:
In this short 5 minute thigh workout you will learn how to sculpt strong ballet legs at home with no equipment. Find something to hold onto (the back of a chair, or kitchen worktop if you don’t have a ballet barre) and spend just 5 minutes a day to sculpt toned, lean and strong ballet legs. This is the best thigh exercise to feel the burn and tone your inner and outer thighs. It is the perfect leg workout if you are short on time.

I specialise in combining ballet technique and fitness to provide you with short workouts that are both achievable and sustainable in the long-term.

In a past life, I was a busy corporate lawyer, working crazy long hours with little time to focus on my health and fitness.

snippet.title: Stop Dropping Your Baby - An Intro to Reparenting Your Inner Child
snippet.description:
Are you ready to join that NOBB Life? 
https://lnk.bio/ER6J

Our childhood is where the subconscious mind is formed.

It’s also where we learn how we process emotions, what relationships look like, how to hold boundaries, and countless other habits and behaviors.

Ideally, our parents are two self actualized people who allow their children to be seen and heard as the unique individual they are. The reality is that we live in a culture that does not teach conscious awareness, so most of us are born to unconscious parents.

Unconscious parents are repeating the same habits and patterns they’ve learned. They’re operating from a wounded space because of their own unprocessed emotions.
It’s important to understand that parents can only parent from their own level of awareness.

We can only give others what we have practiced giving ourselves.

I work with mostly Black woman. Over time I’ve come to understand while they seek help for different reasons I can generalized reasons to feeling of low-self worth. Each of these issues manifest differently, but they’re all tied to one thing: conditioned behavior practiced since childhood. #NOBB #NOBBLIFE

00:30 - 02:18 What are Unconscious Parents?
03:45 - 04:27 What is reparenting?
04:27 - 07:17 My Story: Low Self- Worth at 6 & High Functioning Anxiety by 12 
07:18 - 09:12 The Wounded Inner Child of Many Black Women
09:13 - 11:08 How to NOT Blame Your Parents

localized.title: Stop Dropping Your Baby - An Intro to Reparenting Your Inner Child
localized.description:
Are you ready to join that NOBB Life? 
https://lnk.bio/ER6J

Our childhood is where the subconscious mind is formed.

It’s also where we learn how we process emotions, what relationships look like, how to hold boundaries, and countless other habits and behaviors.

Ideally, our parents are two self actualized people who allow their children to be seen and heard as the unique individual they are. The reality is that we live in a culture that does not teach conscious awareness, so most of us are born to unconscious parents.

Unconscious parents are repeating the same habits and patterns they’ve learned. They’re operating from a wounded space because of their own unprocessed emotions.
It’s important to understand that parents can only parent from their own level of awareness.

We can only give others what we have practiced giving ourselves.

I work with mostly Black woman. Over time I’ve come to understand while they seek help for different reasons I can generalized reasons to feeling of low-self worth. Each of these issues manifest differently, but they’re all tied to one thing: conditioned behavior practiced since childhood. #NOBB #NOBBLIFE

snippet.title: How To Improve Your Child's Health, Development, and Behaviour
snippet.description:
Parents, do you want your child to have better control of their emotions and behaviour? How does your home environment affect your child's development? Get the most practical answers here in this episode with Dr. Leila Masson, a consultant paediatrician who specializes in nutritional and environmental medicine for children.


SPEAKER BACKGROUND:

Dr Leila  Masson is a consultant paediatrician who specializes in nutritional and environmental medicine for children. She is the mother of two wonderful, grown-up boys. She had a busy clinic in Auckland, New Zealand, for 14 years before moving to Sydney in 2016. She received her medical doctorate from the Free University of Berlin and did her paediatric specialist training at the University of California in San Francisco. She received her Master in Public Health from Harvard University and her Diploma in Tropical Medicine from the London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine. 

Leila has worked in the US, Europe, New Zealand, and volunteered for 2 years setting up a rural clinic in Pakistan. Dr Masson lectures internationally on the subject of children’s nutrition and an integrative medicine approach to pediatric issues, including autism spectrum disorders, ADHD, behaviour issues, allergies, recurrent infections, and autoimmune diseases. She is the author of “Children’s Health A-Z”,  a parent’s practical guide to natural and effective therapies for the most common health issues in childhood.  Visit her website at https://www.drleilamasson.com/
